uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor

Class IClassifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.IReasonerDefault
      • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.IClassifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IReasoner
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NClassifier

    public abstract class IClassifier
extends IReasonerDefault
    Provides classification-based versions of the reasoning mechanisms defined by IReasoner. This is an abstract class that leaves the implementatation of the actual classification mechanisms to the derived class.

    The instance-level frame/slot-networks representations of instances that are passed into the classify(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.IFrame, uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.IClassifierOps) method will be "free-instance" copies of the originals (see IFreeCopier).

        public java.util.Set<IUpdateOp> reinitialiseFrame(IEditor iEditor,
                                                  IFrame frame,
                                                  java.util.Set<IUpdateOp> ops)
        Performs any required updates on specified de-serilaized instance-level frame to bring it into line with the latest version of the model, which may have been updated since frame was serilaized. Updates will include any required updates to set of slots, plus any of the other specified update operations that apply.

        Overrides:

        iEditor - Model-instantiation editor
        frame - Frame to be re-initialised
        ops - Types of update operations to be performed (in addition to any required slot update operations)
        Returns:
